HEADWORD: Afoot
<hw>A*foot"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>foot</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>On
foot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We 'll walk <qex>afoot</qex> a while.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: In motion; in action; astir; in
progress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The matter being <qex>afoot</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Afore</ent>⟦br⟧
